===Etymology===
Middle English ''fox'', Old English ''fox'', from common Germanic ''*fuhsaz'', from Proto-Indo-European ''*puk-so-'', derived from ''*peuk-'' "thick-haired".  Cognates include German [[Fuchs]], Frisian [[foks]], and Dutch [[vos]].

